summary: Seriously why did they made Jonah say Ultimate is not a real sport!? It makes no sense for the character, and it sucks when a...
question: Seriously why did they made Jonah say Ultimate is not a real sport!? It makes no sense for the character, and it sucks when a sport is socially invalidated due to cultural stereotypes!
answer: Cultural stereotypes? I’m not quite sure what you mean by that but as for the first question yeah I don’t know cause it feels like a weird thing to have him say after him going away to frisbee camp specifically cause he wanted to be good enough for an elite ultimate team. It just seems like the writers didn’t see any where else to go with it and are dropping it without build up. This is just another instance of 2b’s bad writing biting the writers in the ass cause they seem to know where they want to go now whereas it just seemed like they were jogging in place with no sense of direction last season.

summary: Back in September, I gave an informative speech in my college speech class about Andi Mack. Today, I am clearing out old papers...
body: Back in September, I gave an informative speech in my college speech class about Andi Mack. Today, I am clearing out old papers and found this anonymous peer comment: “Can’t believe this is the 1st Disney show w/ gay relationship + multiracial parents” and reading that makes my heart hurt a little. Because canonically, we only have a gay *character* and not a relationship. Tyrus, so many of us are counting on you. Even random college students who have never watched the show. (((Sidenote: this student also said “‘friendom’ kind of surprised me.” Aka you guys are pretty legendary.)))
